               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1399" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1399" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1399" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1399" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH RICHARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of James Richards, of Union-street. On Saturday the 6th of Jan., before eight o'clock at night, the pri<lb></lb>soner came and asked for the "Illustrated London News," "Bell's Life," and "Parley's Penny Library"—I said, "Bell's Life" was 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and he said be would only take the two newspapers, which came to 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I gave him the two papers—he laid down a counterfeit shilling—I said that would not do, and he ran away—he had not gone out of the shop when I said it was bad—I spoke to a man at the door, who brought him back—I marked the shilling, and gave it to the policeman—I had showed it to my husband, but do not think I lost sight of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CROUCH</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> He did not turn back when you objected to the shilling? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, he ran out—he must have heard me say it was bad, unless he was deaf—I do not know whether I spoke as low as I do now—I held the shilling in my hand till my husband came in, which was in about two minutes—the prisoner had the newspapers when he was brought back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1400" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1400" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1400" type="surname" value="O'NEIL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1400" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>PETER O'NEIL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I was on duty in Union-street, on the 6th of Jan., and saw a crowd at Richards's shop—I went in, and Mrs. Richards gave me 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1401" type="witnessName">
